I completed my medical school at John Burns School of Medicine in 1984. After one year of internship at Saint Mary's Hospital, I completed five years of residency in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation Hawaii, San Francisco, and Stanford including the last year as a Chief Resident.
In 1990, I joined the VA Palo Alto Health Care system under the departments of polytrauma, pain medicine and PM&R as a Staff Physician and from 2008-2009, I became the Medical Director and Senior Physiatrist in the Polytrauma System of Care, and the Chief of Service of PM&R.
